48 void
49 testInstanceCreate()
50 {
51 testcase("Instance Create");
52
53 using namespace jtx;
54
55 // XRP to IOU
56 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env&) {
57 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectBalances(
58 XRP(10'000), USD(10'000), IOUAmount{10'000'000, 0}));
59 });
60
61 // IOU to IOU
62 testAMM(
63 [&](AMM& ammAlice, Env&) {
64 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectBalances(
65 USD(20'000), BTC(0.5), IOUAmount{100, 0}));
66 },
67 {{USD(20'000), BTC(0.5)}});
68
69 // IOU to IOU + transfer fee
70 {
71 Env env{*this};
72 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(20'000), BTC(0.5)}, Fund::All);
73 env(rate(gw, 1.25));
74 env.close();
75 // no transfer fee on create
76 AMM ammAlice(env, alice, USD(20'000), BTC(0.5));
77 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectBalances(
78 USD(20'000), BTC(0.5), IOUAmount{100, 0}));
79 BEAST_EXPECT(expectLine(env, alice, USD(0)));
80 BEAST_EXPECT(expectLine(env, alice, BTC(0)));
81 }
82
83 // Require authorization is set, account is authorized
84 {
85 Env env{*this};
86 env.fund(XRP(30'000), gw, alice);
87 env.close();
88 env(fset(gw, asfRequireAuth));
89 env(trust(alice, gw["USD"](30'000), 0));
90 env(trust(gw, alice["USD"](0), tfSetfAuth));
91 env.close();
92 env(pay(gw, alice, USD(10'000)));
93 env.close();
94 AMM ammAlice(env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000));
95 }
96
97 // Cleared global freeze
98 {
99 Env env{*this};
100 env.fund(XRP(30'000), gw, alice);
101 env.close();
102 env.trust(USD(30'000), alice);
103 env.close();
104 env(pay(gw, alice, USD(10'000)));
105 env.close();
106 env(fset(gw, asfGlobalFreeze));
107 env.close();
108 AMM ammAliceFail(
109 env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000), ter(tecFROZEN));
110 env(fclear(gw, asfGlobalFreeze));
111 env.close();
112 AMM ammAlice(env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000));
113 }
114
115 // Trading fee
116 testAMM(
117 [&](AMM& amm, Env&) {
118 BEAST_EXPECT(amm.expectTradingFee(1'000));
119 BEAST_EXPECT(amm.expectAuctionSlot(100, 0, IOUAmount{0}));
120 },
121 std::nullopt,
122 1'000);
123
124 // Make sure asset comparison works.
125 BEAST_EXPECT(
126 STIssue(sfAsset, STAmount(XRP(2'000)).issue()) ==
127 STIssue(sfAsset, STAmount(XRP(2'000)).issue()));
128 BEAST_EXPECT(
129 STIssue(sfAsset, STAmount(XRP(2'000)).issue()) !=
130 STIssue(sfAsset, STAmount({USD(2'000)}).issue()));
131 }

133 void
134 testInvalidInstance()
135 {
136 testcase("Invalid Instance");
137
138 using namespace jtx;
139
140 // Can't have both XRP tokens
141 {
142 Env env{*this};
143 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
144 AMM ammAlice(
145 env, alice, XRP(10'000), XRP(10'000), ter(temBAD_AMM_TOKENS));
146 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
147 }
148
149 // Can't have both tokens the same IOU
150 {
151 Env env{*this};
152 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
153 AMM ammAlice(
154 env, alice, USD(10'000), USD(10'000), ter(temBAD_AMM_TOKENS));
155 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
156 }
157
158 // Can't have zero or negative amounts
159 {
160 Env env{*this};
161 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
162 AMM ammAlice(env, alice, XRP(0), USD(10'000), ter(temBAD_AMOUNT));
163 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
164 AMM ammAlice1(env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(0), ter(temBAD_AMOUNT));
165 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice1.ammExists());
166 AMM ammAlice2(
167 env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(-10'000), ter(temBAD_AMOUNT));
168 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice2.ammExists());
169 AMM ammAlice3(
170 env, alice, XRP(-10'000), USD(10'000), ter(temBAD_AMOUNT));
171 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice3.ammExists());
172 }
173
174 // Bad currency
175 {
176 Env env{*this};
177 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
178 AMM ammAlice(
179 env, alice, XRP(10'000), BAD(10'000), ter(temBAD_CURRENCY));
180 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
181 }
182
183 // Insufficient IOU balance
184 {
185 Env env{*this};
186 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
187 AMM ammAlice(
188 env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(40'000), ter(tecUNFUNDED_AMM));
189 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
190 }
191
192 // Insufficient XRP balance
193 {
194 Env env{*this};
195 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
196 AMM ammAlice(
197 env, alice, XRP(40'000), USD(10'000), ter(tecUNFUNDED_AMM));
198 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
199 }
200
201 // Invalid trading fee
202 {
203 Env env{*this};
204 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {USD(30'000)}, Fund::All);
205 AMM ammAlice(
206 env,
207 alice,
208 XRP(10'000),
209 USD(10'000),
210 false,
211 65'001,
212 10,
213 std::nullopt,
214 std::nullopt,
215 std::nullopt,
216 ter(temBAD_FEE));
217 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());
218 }

278 // Globally frozen
279 {
280 Env env{*this};
281 env.fund(XRP(30'000), gw, alice);
282 env.close();
283 env(fset(gw, asfGlobalFreeze));
284 env.close();
285 env(trust(gw, alice["USD"](30'000)));
286 env.close();
287 AMM ammAlice(env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000), ter(tecFROZEN));
288 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());

292 {
293 Env env{*this};
294 env.fund(XRP(30'000), gw, alice);
295 env.close();
296 env(trust(gw, alice["USD"](30'000)));
297 env.close();
298 env(trust(gw, alice["USD"](0), tfSetFreeze));
299 env.close();
300 AMM ammAlice(env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000), ter(tecFROZEN));
301 BEAST_EXPECT(!ammAlice.ammExists());

304 // Insufficient reserve, XRP/IOU
305 {
306 Env env(*this);
307 auto const starting_xrp =
308 XRP(1'000) + reserve(env, 3) + env.current()->fees().base * 4;
309 env.fund(starting_xrp, gw);
310 env.fund(starting_xrp, alice);
311 env.trust(USD(2'000), alice);
312 env.close();
313 env(pay(gw, alice, USD(2'000)));
314 env.close();
315 env(offer(alice, XRP(101), USD(100)));
316 env(offer(alice, XRP(102), USD(100)));
317 AMM ammAlice(
318 env, alice, XRP(1'000), USD(1'000), ter(tecUNFUNDED_AMM));
319 }
320
321 // Insufficient reserve, IOU/IOU
322 {
323 Env env(*this);
324 auto const starting_xrp =
325 reserve(env, 4) + env.current()->fees().base * 5;
326 env.fund(starting_xrp, gw);
327 env.fund(starting_xrp, alice);
328 env.trust(USD(2'000), alice);
329 env.trust(EUR(2'000), alice);
330 env.close();
331 env(pay(gw, alice, USD(2'000)));
332 env(pay(gw, alice, EUR(2'000)));
333 env.close();
334 env(offer(alice, EUR(101), USD(100)));
335 env(offer(alice, EUR(102), USD(100)));
336 AMM ammAlice(
337 env, alice, EUR(1'000), USD(1'000), ter(tecINSUF_RESERVE_LINE));
338 }
339
340 // Insufficient fee
341 {
342 Env env(*this);
343 fund(env, gw, {alice}, XRP(2'000), {USD(2'000), EUR(2'000)});
344 AMM ammAlice(
345 env,
346 alice,
347 EUR(1'000),
348 USD(1'000),
349 false,
350 0,
351 ammCrtFee(env).drops() - 1,
352 std::nullopt,
353 std::nullopt,
354 std::nullopt,
355 ter(telINSUF_FEE_P));
356 }

358 // AMM with LPTokens
359
360 // AMM with one LPToken from another AMM.
361 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
362 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {EUR(10'000)}, Fund::IOUOnly);
363 AMM ammAMMToken(
364 env,
365 alice,
366 EUR(10'000),
367 STAmount{ammAlice.lptIssue(), 1'000'000},
368 ter(tecAMM_INVALID_TOKENS));
369 AMM ammAMMToken1(
370 env,
371 alice,
372 STAmount{ammAlice.lptIssue(), 1'000'000},
373 EUR(10'000),
374 ter(tecAMM_INVALID_TOKENS));
375 });
376
377 // AMM with two LPTokens from other AMMs.
378 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
379 fund(env, gw, {alice}, {EUR(10'000)}, Fund::IOUOnly);
380 AMM ammAlice1(env, alice, XRP(10'000), EUR(10'000));
381 auto const token1 = ammAlice.lptIssue();
382 auto const token2 = ammAlice1.lptIssue();
383 AMM ammAMMTokens(
384 env,
385 alice,
386 STAmount{token1, 1'000'000},
387 STAmount{token2, 1'000'000},
388 ter(tecAMM_INVALID_TOKENS));
389 });
390
391 // Issuer has DefaultRipple disabled
392 {
393 Env env(*this);
394 env.fund(XRP(30'000), gw);
395 env(fclear(gw, asfDefaultRipple));
396 AMM ammGw(env, gw, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000), ter(terNO_RIPPLE));
397 env.fund(XRP(30'000), alice);
398 env.trust(USD(30'000), alice);
399 env(pay(gw, alice, USD(30'000)));
400 AMM ammAlice(
401 env, alice, XRP(10'000), USD(10'000), ter(terNO_RIPPLE));
402 Account const gw1("gw1");
403 env.fund(XRP(30'000), gw1);
404 env(fclear(gw1, asfDefaultRipple));
405 env.trust(USD(30'000), gw1);
406 env(pay(gw, gw1, USD(30'000)));
407 auto const USD1 = gw1["USD"];
408 AMM ammGwGw1(env, gw, USD(10'000), USD1(10'000), ter(terNO_RIPPLE));
409 env.trust(USD1(30'000), alice);
410 env(pay(gw1, alice, USD1(30'000)));
411 AMM ammAlice1(
412 env, alice, USD(10'000), USD1(10'000), ter(terNO_RIPPLE));
413 }
414
415 // Issuer has clawback enabled
416 {
417 Env env(*this);
418 env.fund(XRP(1'000), gw);
419 env(fset(gw, asfAllowTrustLineClawback));
420 fund(env, gw, {alice}, XRP(1'000), {USD(1'000)}, Fund::Acct);
421 env.close();
422 AMM amm(env, gw, XRP(100), USD(100), ter(tecNO_PERMISSION));
423 AMM amm1(env, alice, USD(100), XRP(100), ter(tecNO_PERMISSION));
424 env(fclear(gw, asfAllowTrustLineClawback));
425 env.close();
426 // Can't be cleared
427 AMM amm2(env, gw, XRP(100), USD(100), ter(tecNO_PERMISSION));
428 }

1234
1235 // Equal deposit: 1000000 tokens, 10% of the current pool
1236 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
1237 ammAlice.deposit(carol, 1'000'000);
1238 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectBalances(
1239 XRP(11'000), USD(11'000), IOUAmount{11'000'000, 0}));
1240 // 30,000 less deposited 1,000
1241 BEAST_EXPECT(expectLine(env, carol, USD(29'000)));
1242 // 30,000 less deposited 1,000 and 10 drops tx fee
1243 BEAST_EXPECT(
1244 expectLedgerEntryRoot(env, carol, XRPAmount{28'999'999'990}));
1245 });
1246
1247 // equal asset deposit: unit test to exercise the rounding-down of
1248 // LPTokens in the AMMHelpers.cpp: adjustLPTokens calculations
1249 // The LPTokens need to have 16 significant digits and a fractional part
1250 for (const Number deltaLPTokens :
1251 {Number{UINT64_C(100000'0000000009), -10},
1252 Number{UINT64_C(100000'0000000001), -10}})
1253 {
1254 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
1255 // initial LPToken balance
1256 IOUAmount const initLPToken = ammAlice.getLPTokensBalance();
1257 const IOUAmount newLPTokens{
1258 deltaLPTokens.mantissa(), deltaLPTokens.exponent()};
1259
1260 // carol performs a two-asset deposit
1261 ammAlice.deposit(
1262 DepositArg{.account = carol, .tokens = newLPTokens});
1263
1264 IOUAmount const finalLPToken = ammAlice.getLPTokensBalance();
1265
1266 // Change in behavior due to rounding down of LPTokens:
1267 // there is a decrease in the observed return of LPTokens --
1268 // Inputs Number{UINT64_C(100000'0000000001), -10} and
1269 // Number{UINT64_C(100000'0000000009), -10} are both rounded
1270 // down to 1e5
1271 BEAST_EXPECT((finalLPToken - initLPToken == IOUAmount{1, 5}));
1272 BEAST_EXPECT(finalLPToken - initLPToken < deltaLPTokens);
1273
1274 // fraction of newLPTokens/(existing LPToken balance). The
1275 // existing LPToken balance is 1e7
1276 const Number fr = deltaLPTokens / 1e7;
1277
1278 // The below equations are based on Equation 1, 2 from XLS-30d
1279 // specification, Section: 2.3.1.2
1280 const Number deltaXRP = fr * 1e10;
1281 const Number deltaUSD = fr * 1e4;
1282
1283 const STAmount depositUSD =
1284 STAmount{USD, deltaUSD.mantissa(), deltaUSD.exponent()};
1285
1286 const STAmount depositXRP =
1287 STAmount{XRP, deltaXRP.mantissa(), deltaXRP.exponent()};
1288
1289 // initial LPTokens (1e7) + newLPTokens
1290 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectBalances(
1291 XRP(10'000) + depositXRP,
1292 USD(10'000) + depositUSD,
1293 IOUAmount{1, 7} + newLPTokens));
1294
1295 // 30,000 less deposited depositUSD
1296 BEAST_EXPECT(expectLine(env, carol, USD(30'000) - depositUSD));
1297 // 30,000 less deposited depositXRP and 10 drops tx fee
1298 BEAST_EXPECT(expectLedgerEntryRoot(
1299 env, carol, XRP(30'000) - depositXRP - txfee(env, 1)));
1300 });
1301 }

2399 void
2400 testFeeVote()
2401 {
2402 testcase("Fee Vote");
2403 using namespace jtx;
2404
2405 // One vote sets fee to 1%.
2406 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2407 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectAuctionSlot(0, 0, IOUAmount{0}));
2408 ammAlice.vote({}, 1'000);
2409 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(1'000));
2410 // Discounted fee is 1/10 of trading fee.
2411 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectAuctionSlot(100, 0, IOUAmount{0}));
2412 });
2413
2414 auto vote = [&](AMM& ammAlice,
2415 Env& env,
2416 int i,
2417 int fundUSD = 100'000,
2418 std::uint32_t tokens = 10'000'000,
2419 std::vector<Account>* accounts = nullptr) {
2420 Account a(std::to_string(i));
2421 fund(env, gw, {a}, {USD(fundUSD)}, Fund::Acct);
2422 ammAlice.deposit(a, tokens);
2423 ammAlice.vote(a, 50 * (i + 1));
2424 if (accounts)
2425 accounts->push_back(std::move(a));
2426 };
2427
2428 // Eight votes fill all voting slots, set fee 0.175%.
2429 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2430 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2431 vote(ammAlice, env, i, 10'000);
2432 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(175));
2433 });
2434
2435 // Eight votes fill all voting slots, set fee 0.175%.
2436 // New vote, same account, sets fee 0.225%
2437 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2438 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2439 vote(ammAlice, env, i);
2440 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(175));
2441 Account const a("0");
2442 ammAlice.vote(a, 450);
2443 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(225));
2444 });
2445
2446 // Eight votes fill all voting slots, set fee 0.175%.
2447 // New vote, new account, higher vote weight, set higher fee 0.244%
2448 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2449 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2450 vote(ammAlice, env, i);
2451 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(175));
2452 vote(ammAlice, env, 7, 100'000, 20'000'000);
2453 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(244));
2454 });
2455
2456 // Eight votes fill all voting slots, set fee 0.219%.
2457 // New vote, new account, higher vote weight, set smaller fee 0.206%
2458 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2459 for (int i = 7; i > 0; --i)
2460 vote(ammAlice, env, i);
2461 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(219));
2462 vote(ammAlice, env, 0, 100'000, 20'000'000);
2463 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(206));
2464 });
2465
2466 // Eight votes fill all voting slots. The accounts then withdraw all
2467 // tokens. An account sets a new fee and the previous slots are
2468 // deleted.
2469 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2470 std::vector<Account> accounts;
2471 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2472 vote(ammAlice, env, i, 100'000, 10'000'000, &accounts);
2473 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(175));
2474 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2475 ammAlice.withdrawAll(accounts[i]);
2476 ammAlice.deposit(carol, 10'000'000);
2477 ammAlice.vote(carol, 1'000);
2478 // The initial LP set the fee to 1000. Carol gets 50% voting
2479 // power, and the new fee is 500.
2480 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(500));
2481 });
2482
2483 // Eight votes fill all voting slots. The accounts then withdraw some
2484 // tokens. The new vote doesn't get the voting power but
2485 // the slots are refreshed and the fee is updated.
2486 testAMM([&](AMM& ammAlice, Env& env) {
2487 std::vector<Account> accounts;
2488 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2489 vote(ammAlice, env, i, 100'000, 10'000'000, &accounts);
2490 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(175));
2491 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i)
2492 ammAlice.withdraw(accounts[i], 9'000'000);
2493 ammAlice.deposit(carol, 1'000);
2494 // The vote is not added to the slots
2495 ammAlice.vote(carol, 1'000);
2496 auto const info = ammAlice.ammRpcInfo()[jss::amm][jss::vote_slots];
2497 for (std::uint16_t i = 0; i < info.size(); ++i)
2498 BEAST_EXPECT(info[i][jss::account] != carol.human());
2499 // But the slots are refreshed and the fee is changed
2500 BEAST_EXPECT(ammAlice.expectTradingFee(82));
2501 });
2502 }

2504 void
2505 testInvalidBid()
2506 {
2507 testcase("Invalid Bid");
2508 using namespace jtx;
2509 using namespace std::chrono;
2510
2511 // burn all the LPTokens through a AMMBid transaction
2512 {
2513 Env env(*this);
2514 fund(env, gw, {alice}, XRP(2'000), {USD(2'000)});
2515 AMM amm(env, gw, XRP(1'000), USD(1'000), false, 1'000);
2516
2517 // auction slot is owned by the creator of the AMM i.e. gw
2518 BEAST_EXPECT(amm.expectAuctionSlot(100, 0, IOUAmount{0}));
2519
2520 // gw attempts to burn all her LPTokens through a bid transaction
2521 // this transaction fails because AMMBid transaction can not burn
2522 // all the outstanding LPTokens
2523 env(amm.bid({
2524 .account = gw,
2525 .bidMin = 1'000'000,
2526 }),
2527 ter(tecAMM_INVALID_TOKENS));
2528 }
2529
2530 // burn all the LPTokens through a AMMBid transaction
2531 {
2532 Env env(*this);
2533 fund(env, gw, {alice}, XRP(2'000), {USD(2'000)});
2534 AMM amm(env, gw, XRP(1'000), USD(1'000), false, 1'000);
2535
2536 // auction slot is owned by the creator of the AMM i.e. gw
2537 BEAST_EXPECT(amm.expectAuctionSlot(100, 0, IOUAmount{0}));
2538
2539 // gw burns all but one of its LPTokens through a bid transaction
2540 // this transaction suceeds because the bid price is less than
2541 // the total outstanding LPToken balance
2542 env(amm.bid({
2543 .account = gw,
2544 .bidMin = STAmount{amm.lptIssue(), UINT64_C(999'999)},
2545 }),
2546 ter(tesSUCCESS))
2547 .close();
2548
2549 // gw must own the auction slot
2550 BEAST_EXPECT(amm.expectAuctionSlot(100, 0, IOUAmount{999'999}));
2551

2553 BEAST_EXPECT(
2554 amm.expectBalances(XRP(1'000), USD(1'000), IOUAmount{1}));
2555
2556 // gw owns only 1 LPToken in its balance
2557 BEAST_EXPECT(Number{amm.getLPTokensBalance(gw)} == 1);
2558
2559 // gw attempts to burn the last of its LPTokens in an AMMBid
2560 // transaction. This transaction fails because it would burn all
2561 // the remaining LPTokens
2562 env(amm.bid({
2563 .account = gw,
2564 .bidMin = 1,
2565 }),
2566 ter(tecAMM_INVALID_TOKENS));
2567 }

3998 void
3999 testRippling()
4000 {
4001 testcase("Rippling");
4002 using namespace jtx;
4003
4004 // Rippling via AMM fails because AMM trust line has 0 limit.
4005 // Set up two issuers, A and B. Have each issue a token called TST.
4006 // Have another account C hold TST from both issuers,
4007 // and create an AMM for this pair.
4008 // Have a fourth account, D, create a trust line to the AMM for TST.
4009 // Send a payment delivering TST.AMM from C to D, using SendMax in
4010 // TST.A (or B) and a path through the AMM account. By normal
4011 // rippling rules, this would have caused the AMM's balances
4012 // to shift at a 1:1 rate with no fee applied has it not been
4013 // for 0 limit.
4014 {
4015 Env env(*this);
4016 auto const A = Account("A");
4017 auto const B = Account("B");
4018 auto const TSTA = A["TST"];
4019 auto const TSTB = B["TST"];
4020 auto const C = Account("C");
4021 auto const D = Account("D");
4022
4023 env.fund(XRP(10'000), A);
4024 env.fund(XRP(10'000), B);
4025 env.fund(XRP(10'000), C);
4026 env.fund(XRP(10'000), D);
4027
4028 env.trust(TSTA(10'000), C);
4029 env.trust(TSTB(10'000), C);
4030 env(pay(A, C, TSTA(10'000)));
4031 env(pay(B, C, TSTB(10'000)));
4032 AMM amm(env, C, TSTA(5'000), TSTB(5'000));
4033 auto const ammIss = Issue(TSTA.currency, amm.ammAccount());
4034
4035 // Can SetTrust only for AMM LP tokens
4036 env(trust(D, STAmount{ammIss, 10'000}), ter(tecNO_PERMISSION));
4037 env.close();
4038
4039 // The payment would fail because of above, but check just in case
4040 env(pay(C, D, STAmount{ammIss, 10}),
4041 sendmax(TSTA(100)),
4042 path(amm.ammAccount()),
4043 txflags(tfPartialPayment | tfNoRippleDirect),
4044 ter(tecPATH_DRY));
4045 }
4046 }

4048 void
4049 testAMMAndCLOB()
4050 {
4051 testcase("AMMAndCLOB, offer quality change");
4052 using namespace jtx;
4053 auto const gw = Account("gw");
4054 auto const TST = gw["TST"];
4055 auto const LP1 = Account("LP1");
4056 auto const LP2 = Account("LP2");
4057
4058 auto prep = [&](auto const& offerCb, auto const& expectCb) {
4059 Env env(*this);
4060 env.fund(XRP(30'000'000'000), gw);
4061 env(offer(gw, XRP(11'500'000'000), TST(1'000'000'000)));
4062
4063 env.fund(XRP(10'000), LP1);
4064 env.fund(XRP(10'000), LP2);
4065 env(offer(LP1, TST(25), XRPAmount(287'500'000)));
4066
4067 // Either AMM or CLOB offer
4068 offerCb(env);
4069
4070 env(offer(LP2, TST(25), XRPAmount(287'500'000)));
4071
4072 expectCb(env);
4073 };
4074
4075 // If we replace AMM with equivalent CLOB offer, which
4076 // AMM generates when it is consumed, then the
4077 // result must be identical.
4078 std::string lp2TSTBalance;
4079 std::string lp2TakerGets;
4080 std::string lp2TakerPays;
4081 // Execute with AMM first
4082 prep(
4083 [&](Env& env) { AMM amm(env, LP1, TST(25), XRP(250)); },
4084 [&](Env& env) {
4085 lp2TSTBalance =
4086 getAccountLines(env, LP2, TST)["lines"][0u]["balance"]
4087 .asString();
4088 auto const offer = getAccountOffers(env, LP2)["offers"][0u];
4089 lp2TakerGets = offer["taker_gets"].asString();
4090 lp2TakerPays = offer["taker_pays"]["value"].asString();
4091 });
4092 // Execute with CLOB offer
4093 prep(
4094 [&](Env& env) {
4095 env(offer(
4096 LP1,
4097 XRPAmount{18'095'133},
4098 STAmount{TST, UINT64_C(1'68737984885388), -14}),
4099 txflags(tfPassive));
4100 },
4101 [&](Env& env) {
4102 BEAST_EXPECT(
4103 lp2TSTBalance ==
4104 getAccountLines(env, LP2, TST)["lines"][0u]["balance"]
4105 .asString());
4106 auto const offer = getAccountOffers(env, LP2)["offers"][0u];
4107 BEAST_EXPECT(lp2TakerGets == offer["taker_gets"].asString());
4108 BEAST_EXPECT(
4109 lp2TakerPays == offer["taker_pays"]["value"].asString());
4110 });
4111 }

4739 void
4740 testSelection()
4741 {
4742 testcase("Offer/Strand Selection");
4743 using namespace jtx;
4744 Account const ed("ed");
4745 Account const gw1("gw1");
4746 auto const ETH = gw1["ETH"];
4747 auto const CAN = gw1["CAN"];
4748
4749 // These tests are expected to fail if the OwnerPaysFee feature
4750 // is ever supported. Updates will need to be made to AMM handling
4751 // in the payment engine, and these tests will need to be updated.
4752
4753 auto prep = [&](Env& env, auto gwRate, auto gw1Rate) {
4754 fund(env, gw, {alice, carol, bob, ed}, XRP(2'000), {USD(2'000)});
4755 env.fund(XRP(2'000), gw1);
4756 fund(
4757 env,
4758 gw1,
4759 {alice, carol, bob, ed},
4760 {ETH(2'000), CAN(2'000)},
4761 Fund::IOUOnly);
4762 env(rate(gw, gwRate));
4763 env(rate(gw1, gw1Rate));
4764 env.close();
4765 };
4766
4767 for (auto const& rates :
4768 {std::make_pair(1.5, 1.9), std::make_pair(1.9, 1.5)})
4769 {
4770 // Offer Selection
4771
4772 // Cross-currency payment: AMM has the same spot price quality
4773 // as CLOB's offer and can't generate a better quality offer.
4774 // The transfer fee in this case doesn't change the CLOB quality
4775 // because trIn is ignored on adjustment and trOut on payment is
4776 // also ignored because ownerPaysTransferFee is false in this case.
4777 // Run test for 0) offer, 1) AMM, 2) offer and AMM
4778 // to verify that the quality is better in the first case,
4779 // and CLOB is selected in the second case.
4780 {
4781 std::array<Quality, 3> q;
4782 for (auto i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
4783 {
4784 Env env(*this);
4785 prep(env, rates.first, rates.second);
4786 std::optional<AMM> amm;
4787 if (i == 0 || i == 2)
4788 {
4789 env(offer(ed, ETH(400), USD(400)), txflags(tfPassive));
4790 env.close();
4791 }
4792 if (i > 0)
4793 amm.emplace(env, ed, USD(1'000), ETH(1'000));
4794 env(pay(carol, bob, USD(100)),
4795 path(~USD),
4796 sendmax(ETH(500)));
4797 env.close();
4798 // CLOB and AMM, AMM is not selected
4799 if (i == 2)
4800 {
4801 BEAST_EXPECT(amm->expectBalances(
4802 USD(1'000), ETH(1'000), amm->tokens()));
4803 }
4804 BEAST_EXPECT(expectLine(env, bob, USD(2'100)));
4805 q[i] = Quality(Amounts{
4806 ETH(2'000) - env.balance(carol, ETH),
4807 env.balance(bob, USD) - USD(2'000)});
4808 }
4809 // CLOB is better quality than AMM
4810 BEAST_EXPECT(q[0] > q[1]);
4811 // AMM is not selected with CLOB
4812 BEAST_EXPECT(q[0] == q[2]);
4813 }
4814 // Offer crossing: AMM has the same spot price quality
4815 // as CLOB's offer and can't generate a better quality offer.
4816 // The transfer fee in this case doesn't change the CLOB quality
4817 // because the quality adjustment is ignored for the offer crossing.
4818 for (auto i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
4819 {
4820 Env env(*this);
4821 prep(env, rates.first, rates.second);
4822 std::optional<AMM> amm;
4823 if (i == 0 || i == 2)
4824 {
4825 env(offer(ed, ETH(400), USD(400)), txflags(tfPassive));
4826 env.close();
4827 }
4828 if (i > 0)
4829 amm.emplace(env, ed, USD(1'000), ETH(1'000));
4830 env(offer(alice, USD(400), ETH(400)));
4831 env.close();
4832 // AMM is not selected
4833 if (i > 0)
4834 {
4835 BEAST_EXPECT(amm->expectBalances(
4836 USD(1'000), ETH(1'000), amm->tokens()));
4837 }
4838 if (i == 0 || i == 2)
4839 {
4840 // Fully crosses
4841 BEAST_EXPECT(expectOffers(env, alice, 0));
4842 }
4843 // Fails to cross because AMM is not selected
4844 else
4845 {
4846 BEAST_EXPECT(expectOffers(
4847 env, alice, 1, {Amounts{USD(400), ETH(400)}}));
4848 }
4849 BEAST_EXPECT(expectOffers(env, ed, 0));
4850 }
4851
4852 // Show that the CLOB quality reduction
4853 // results in AMM offer selection.
4854
4855 // Same as the payment but reduced offer quality
4856 {
4857 std::array<Quality, 3> q;
4858 for (auto i = 0; i < 3; ++i)
4859 {
4860 Env env(*this);
4861 prep(env, rates.first, rates.second);
4862 std::optional<AMM> amm;
4863 if (i == 0 || i == 2)
4864 {

4981 // of two strands, AMM offers have better quality and are consumed
